p2
VJayanthi of Adibhatla
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe 146th Jayanthi of the legendary Adhibhatla Narayana Das of Vizianagaram, a versatile scholar, linguist and exponent of Harikatha, was celebrated at Sri Sivaramakrishna Kshetram by his sishya prasishyas. The programme was conducted by noted Harika\u000atha Bhagavatar Burra Sivaramakrishna Sarma.The function started with the garlanding of the portrait of Narayana Das by M.V. Ravi Kishore, president of Telugu Sampradaya Kalala Parirakshana Samithi. After tributes were paid to Narayana Das by speakers, S. Bharathi Bhagavatar of Eluru, Kondapalli Viswanadham Bhagavatar of Nellore, and Neti Venkataramana Bhagavathar rendered the HarikathasParvathi Parinayam,Tarigonda Vengamamba, andBhaktha Thyagarajurespectively with devotional fervour.In the evening session, N. Padma Bhagavatarini of Repalle rendered the HarikathaSrikrishna Tulabharambrilliantly. Violin vidwan Annavarapu Ramaswami, M.S.K. Kumar of Dharma Prachara Parishat, Neti Visweswara Sarma, and noted scholar Mulukutla Bramhananda Sastri also attended the function.
